						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab lying in a field called Brahmadēvara-hola, about two miles from the village.</hi></p>						

						<p>Āhavamalla (Sōmēśvara I)—A.D. 1044.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 965, Tāraṇa, Chaitra, śu. 5, Tuesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1044, March 6, Tuesday, f.d.t. ·15,</hi> the Śaka year being current.</p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record gifts of land, house-site, etc. It mentions Bhāḷachandrēśvaradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
